26/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- The government announced on Tuesday (August 25th) a large-scale plan to compensate people for losses suffered in the fires raging north of Athens for the past several days.
The cabinet also promised to address the environmental damage.
Government spokesperson Vangelis Antonaros said, "Where there were forests before, new forests will be planted.
No exceptions will be made." According to preliminary data, about 150 houses burned to the ground in the Attica region.
The flames also destroyed about 21,000 hectares of forests.
(Nafthemporiki, Vima - 26/08/09;
AFP - 25/08/09)
